\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Versatile Detector of Pseudo Periodic Patterns
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Augusto Santini, Emiliano Diez, Mariano Llamedo
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
mbox{}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

GIBIO, National Technological University, Buenos Aires, Argentina
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Institute of Physiology, Medical School, National University of Cuyo, Mendoza,
 Argentina
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Introduction
\emph default
: This study aimed to develop a detector with few physiologically-meaningful
 parameters, that could be capable of detecting pseudo periodic patterns.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Materials and Methods
\emph default
: The algorithm is based in a signal detection based on a matched filter,
 and a threshold calculation based on robust stadistics.
 The evaluation of the detector was performed under a corpus consisting
 in two sets.
 One set of human ECGs, and one set of rodent pseudo ECGs.
 The evaluation was performed with respect to the gold standard annotations,
 and was calculated in terms of sensitivity (
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

) and positive predictive value (
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement h
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename /home/augusto/Escritorio/Beca/CINC18 AIPD/images/rhythm.pdf
	width 75text%

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Results
\emph default
: For the human ECG set of recordings, the detector had 100 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 and 99.9 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

, while for the rodent pseudo ECG set of recordings the results where 97.1
 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 and 79.1 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

.
 Both sets results are median values.
 The results obtained under the rodent set where comapred to those obtained
 with another two detectors, where our detector obtained the best results.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Discussion
\emph default
: The algorithm achieved promising results, in a broad set of ECG recordings
 of very different nature, with the addiional capability of further adaptation
 provided by expert assistance.
\end_layout

